~ func_intro
starfish: Great question! Let's explore functions together.  
starfish: A function is a reusable block of code that performs a specific task.  
starfish: Think of it like a recipe: write it once, use it many times!  
starfish: Example: [br]def greet(name): [br]-> print(f"Hello, {name}!") [br]Now you can call it: greet("Hero") â†’ prints "Hello, Hero!"  
