~ why_functions
starfish: Functions make your code better in many ways! [b]1. Reusability:[/b] Write once, use everywhere - instead of copying code 10 times, call the function 10 times! [b]2. Organization:[/b] Break big problems into small pieces. [b]3. Easier to fix:[/b] Change code in one place, not everywhere. [b]4. Easier to read:[/b] Function names explain what the code does.  
starfish: Example: calculate_damage(20, 3) is clearer than seeing 20 * 3 everywhere!  
