~ parameters
starfish: Parameters let functions receive information! They're like variables that get values when you call the function.  
starfish: [b]Function with one parameter:[/b] [br]def greet(name): [br]-> print(f"Welcome, {name}!") [br]Call it: greet("Hero") â†’ prints "Welcome, Hero!"  
starfish: [b]Function with multiple parameters:[/b] [br]def add(a, b): [br]-> print(a + b) [br]Call it: add(5, 3) â†’ prints 8. Separate parameters with commas!  
