~ param_vs_arg
starfish: Good question! They're related but different: [b]Parameter:[/b] The variable in the function definition [br]def greet(name):  â† 'name' is the parameter [b]Argument:[/b] The actual value you pass when calling [br]greet("Alice")  â† "Alice" is the argument  
starfish: Think of it this way: Parameters are the [b]placeholders[/b], Arguments are the [b]actual values[/b]. When you call greet("Bob"), the parameter 'name' becomes "Bob"!  
