~ return_values
starfish: The [b]return[/b] keyword sends a value back from the function! This is different from printing - it lets you use the result!  
starfish: [b]Without return (just prints):[/b] [br]def add(a, b): [br]-> print(a + b)  
starfish: [b]With return (gives back the value):[/b] [br]def add(a, b): [br]-> return a + b [br]Now you can store it: result = add(5, 3) [br]Or use it: print(add(5, 3) * 2) ðŸ’¡ Return stops the function immediately!  
- What's the difference between return and print? => return_vs_print  
- Can I return multiple values? => return_multiple  
