~ return_vs_print
starfish: This confuses many beginners! Let me explain: [b]print():[/b] Shows output to the user, doesn't give back a value, used for displaying information. [b]return:[/b] Sends a value back to your code, the value can be stored or used, used for calculations and data processing.  
starfish: [b]Example:[/b] [br]def calculate(x): [br]-> return x * 2 [br]result = calculate(5)  â† result is 10 [br]print(result)  â† now we display it  
- Can I return multiple values? => return_multiple  
