~ return_multiple
starfish: Yes! Python can return multiple values at once! Just separate them with commas:  
starfish: [br]def get_stats(): [br]-> health = 100 [br]-> mana = 50 [br]-> return health, mana  
starfish: Receive them like this: [br]hp, mp = get_stats() [br]print(hp)  â† prints 100 [br]print(mp)  â† prints 50  
starfish: Behind the scenes, Python returns them as a tuple! You can also do: stats = get_stats() â†’ stats is (100, 50)  
