~ default_values
starfish: Default values make parameters optional! If no argument is passed, the default is used:  
starfish: [br]def greet(name="Traveler"): [br]-> print(f"Hello, {name}!") [br]greet()  â† prints "Hello, Traveler!" [br]greet("Hero")  â† prints "Hello, Hero!"  
starfish: [b]Multiple defaults:[/b] [br]def create_hero(name="Hero", level=1): [br]-> print(f"{name} is level {level}") [br]âš ï¸ Parameters with defaults must come AFTER regular parameters! âœ… def func(a, b=5): â†’ Correct âŒ def func(a=5, b): â†’ Wrong!  
