~ scope
starfish: Scope determines where variables can be accessed! [b]Local scope:[/b] Variables inside a function [br]def my_func(): [br]-> x = 10  â† only exists inside this function [b]Global scope:[/b] Variables outside all functions [br]y = 20  â† exists everywhere [br]def my_func(): [br]-> print(y)  â† can access global y  
starfish: [b]Important rule:[/b] Inside can see outside, Outside CANNOT see inside, Local variables disappear when function ends!  
