~ nested_calls
starfish: Absolutely! Functions can call other functions!  
starfish: [br]def calculate_damage(base): [br]-> return base * 2 [br]def attack(weapon_damage): [br]-> total = calculate_damage(weapon_damage) [br]-> print(f"Dealt {total} damage!") [br]attack(10)  â† prints "Dealt 20 damage!"  
starfish: This helps you break complex tasks into simple steps! Each function does one thing well, then you combine them! [b]Remember:[/b] Define all functions before using them!  
